text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 336, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeffrey Hoogland\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeffrey_Hoogland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carlin was already racing on a warning after his tetchy quarter-final with Kaiya Ota on Thursday, and raised his hand in apology after veering up the track and into Hoogland.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999999998840394, \"rank\": 1.1599713040904616e-10, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"score\": 0.9999998796033723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaiya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaiya\"}, {\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_and_Technical_Training_Center_of_the_Air_Force\", \"score\": 0.9999695531343062, \"rank\": 1.304188478852139e-05, \"text\": \"Ota\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_and_Technical_Training_Center_of_the_Air_Force\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Military_and_Technical_Training_Center_of_the_Air_Force\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoogland\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hoogland\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoogland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoogland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The commissaires decided there was no need for any punishment and the race was restarted, with Carlin having the power to hold off Hoogland down the straight to take his second medal of the week after team sprint silver.\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999999998840394, \"rank\": 1.1599713040904616e-10, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 730, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoogland\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hoogland\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoogland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hoogland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier on,Elinor Barkerand Neah Evans wonOlympicsilver forTeam GBin the women's Madison.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9997333392275045, \"rank\": 0.00026673189953377465, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A big late charge from Barker saw Britain win the last of the 12 sprints in the 120-lap race and move above the Netherlands as Italy's Chiara Consonni and Vittoria Guazzini celebrated gold.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 946, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9927914511469139, \"rank\": 0.007244139450114061, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1024, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8921343667034891, \"rank\": 0.10029391718699585, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9892291153095999, \"rank\": 0.010827804957405963, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1047, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chiara_Consonni\", \"score\": 0.9999999102797159, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chiara Consonni\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chiara_Consonni\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chiara_Consonni\"}, {\"begin\": 1067, \"end\": 1084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vittoria_Guazzini\", \"score\": 0.9999997690024696, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vittoria Guazzini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vittoria_Guazzini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vittoria_Guazzini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy finished with 37 points to Britain's 31 and the Netherlands' 28.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9892291153095999, \"rank\": 0.010827804957405963, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British pair had been on the attack from the off, winning the first sprint and staying in the medal positions for the rest of the race.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1179, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7973113700668046, \"rank\": 0.2503706584085, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They took the most points of any team purely from the sprints, but Italy and the Netherlands both gained a lap on the field, picking up 20 points in the process.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9892291153095999, \"rank\": 0.010827804957405963, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1397, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8921343667034891, \"rank\": 0.10029391718699585, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dame Laura Kenny and Katie Archibald became the first female Olympic champions at the Tokyo Games when the Madison made its debut in the women's programme.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Kenny\"}, {\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\"}, {\"begin\": 1586, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"score\": 0.9997333392275045, \"rank\": 0.00026673189953377465, \"text\": \"Madison\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Madison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barker and Evans are the reigning world champions after their win in Glasgow last summer.\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9998881472111256, \"rank\": 0.00011168624801629832, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evans said: \\\"It's an Olympic silver medal.\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1726, \"end\": 1731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9565770698300009, \"rank\": 0.04539378100511199, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is fantastic.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But as world champions we came in with really high expectations, we wanted to win and we felt we were in a really good position and there was an attack that went that we were not 100 per cent ready for and by the time we responded there was a different race dynamic.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We gave it everything and I think on reflection we will be so proud of the ride we did.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But at the same time when you come for gold it's like, eurgh, not quite.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2219, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But still, silver.\\\"\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 3119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2301, \"end\": 2310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.999451800281471, \"rank\": 0.00046256891104063427, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2410, \"title\":